{{Quote|PORTENTS VAGUE, ASK AGAIN LATER|A Quay novelty toy|<ref name="Fair Prey">{{GamerCite|1|Fair Prey}}</ref>}}
The '''Quay novelty toy''' was a "pre-programmed prognosticator". Comprised of a white [[Plastic/Legends|plastic]] sphere twenty-three [[Centimeter/Legends|centimeters]] in diameter, the toy contained a selection of stored generic answers on a voice chip. When asked a question, a reply was given in a loud voice. The [[Weequay/Legends|Weequay]] [[Species/Legends|species]] believed that the toy was a physical connection to the [[Moon/Legends|Moon]] [[Deity/Legends|God]] [[Quay]], and would consider the answer as though it were of divine origin.

Three Quay novelty toys were collected by the [[Tynnan/Legends|Tynnan]] demolitions expert [[Dawson (Tynnan)|Dawson]] on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] [[Kabal/Legends|Kabal]]. One of the toys was repurposed by Dawson as a makeshift explosive device during the rescue of [[Cecil Noone]] from [[Hunting/Legends|hunter]] [[Tyro Viveca/Legends|Tyro Viveca]]; the resulting detonation killed Viveca and enabled Noone and his crew to escape.

